<h1>From Brigadier General John Sullivan</h1>

<div class="docbody">
<div class="opener">
<table class="salutationBlock">
        <tr>
		<td class="salutationLeft">May it please yr Excellencey</td>
		<td class="salutationRight">Winter Hill March 22d 1776</td>
	      </tr>
      </table>
</div>
<p>being Desired by Capt. Miller Late of Colo. Doolittles Regt to Certify in his favour to Your Excellency I can only Say that he Acted as Capt. in That Regiment till the 26 of Novr then by vote of the Regt (as I was Informed) he Acted as majorI Never knew or heard he had a Commission for that purpose till he Informed me of it yesterday I well remember he gave in his name among the Captains To tarry the present Campaign with a note Annexed that he would Tarry (if promoted) which necessarily Lead me to think he never had a majors Commission. I never heard of Captain Millers Neglecting his Duty in any Respectnor have I Ever heard as I Recollect any thing to his advantage or Disadvantage in the Brigade<a class="ptr" href="#GEWN-03-03-02-0384-fn-0001" id="GEWN-03-03-02-0384-fn-0001-ptr">1</a>This is may it please your Excellencey all that can with truth be Certified by yr Excys most obedt Servt</p>
<div class="closer">
<p class="signed">Jno. Sullivan</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="docback">
<div class="note-source" id="GEWN-03-03-02-0384-sn">

   <p>
<abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Autograph Letter Signed: a letter in the handwriting of, and signed by, the author ]">ALS</abbr>, <span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ U.S. Library of Congress, George Washington Papers, Washington, D.C. ]">DLC:GW</span>.
</p>

</div>
<div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-03-02-0384-fn-0001-ptr" id="GEWN-03-03-02-0384-fn-0001">1</a>
	
   <p>When the <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-03-02-02-0249" class="document">Massachusetts council wrote to GW on 31 Oct. 1775</a> to recommend officers for Col. Ephraim Doolittles Massachusetts regiment, it mistakenly included the name of Jacob Miller (17321812) of Holliston among the officers to be commissioned as ensigns. The council admitted its error in its <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-03-02-02-0499" class="document">letter to GW of 13 Dec. 1775</a> and recommended Miller as major of the regiment. Miller apparently held no rank in the Continental army after 1775, however.</p>

</div>
